This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it deals with automatic taxonomy induction from a set of terms. It also involves the use of multiple sources of information and a policy network to determine the placement of terms on the taxonomy, which are common techniques used in NLP. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL) as it uses reinforcement learning and end-to-end training to optimize the taxonomy induction process. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as taxonomies are often used in information retrieval systems to organize and categorize documents.
